    {"repo": "chromium--2d05e315", "path": "content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc", "symbol": "BrowserMainLoop"},
    {"repo": "chromium--2d05e315", "path": "content/renderer/render_thread_impl.cc", "symbol": "RenderThreadImpl"},
    {"repo": "chromium--2d05e315", "path": "content/browser/child_process_launcher.cc", "symbol": "ChildProcessLauncher"},
    {"repo": "chromium--2d05e315", "path": "content/common/renderer.mojom", "symbol": "Renderer"}
  ],
  "text": "Chromium's multi-process architecture is defined across five key files in the chromium--2d05e315 repo:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** — `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.cc`: The browser-side representation of a renderer process. It manages the lifecycle of a renderer process from the browser's perspective, handling IPC channel setup, process creation, and resource management.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** — `content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc`: The main browser process event loop. It initializes all browser-side subsystems (GPU, audio, network, etc.) and runs the main message loop for the browser process.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** — `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.cc`: The main thread of a renderer process. It runs inside the renderer process, handles IPC messages from the browser, and hosts the Blink rendering engine.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** — `content/browser/child_process_launcher.cc`: Responsible for spawning child processes (renderers, GPU process, plugins, etc.) from the browser process, abstracting platform-specific process creation.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** — `content/common/renderer.mojom`: The Mojo interface declaration for browser-to-renderer communication, defining the IPC contract that the browser uses to control renderer processes."
}

